3
4 A BILL FOR AN ACT ENTITLED: “AN ACT GENERALLY REVISING EDUCATION LAWS; PROHIBITING THE
5 CONSIDERATION OF RACE, COLOR, ETHNICITY, OR NATIONAL ORIGIN BY INSTITUTIONS OF HIGHER
6 EDUCATION IN HIRING, ADMISSIONS, PARTICIPATION, BENEFITS, SCHOLARSHIPS, AND FINANCIAL
7 AID; PROVIDING A PRIVATE CAUSE OF ACTION AND COMPENSATORY DAMAGES, PUNITIVE
8 DAMAGES, STATUTORY DAMAGES, AND INJUNCTIVE AND DECLARATORY RELIEF; WAIVING THE
9 STATE'S CLAIM TO SOVEREIGN IMMUNITY; AND PROVIDING A DELAYED EFFECTIVE DATE.”
10
11 BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATURE OF THE STATE OF MONTANA:
12
13 NEW SECTION. Section 1. Consideration of race, color, ethnicity, or national origin by
14 institution of higher education prohibited -- fair admissions, hiring, and funding -- cause of action. (1) A
15 person may not be excluded from participation in, be denied the benefits of, or be subjected to discrimination by
16 an institution of higher education or by any program or activity in the institution, including affirmative action, on
17 the grounds of race, color, ethnicity, or national origin.
18 (2) An officer, employee, agent, or program or activity of an institution of higher education may not
19 perform actions to further or to facilitate a decision to exclude a person from participation in, deny a person the
20 benefits of, or subject a person to discrimination by the institution on the grounds of race, color, ethnicity, or
21 national origin.
22 (3) An institution of higher education may not use in any way an applicant’s race, color, ethnicity,
23 or national origin to make a decision about the applicant’s admission, scholarships, or financial aid. The use of
24 aggregated data concerning the race, color, ethnicity, or national origin of applicants or students to make any of
25 these decisions is prohibited.
26 (4) (a) An institution of higher education may not reveal or make known to any admissions or
27 financial aid officers data concerning the race, color, national origin, or ethnicity of any applicant or student
28 before admissions and financial aid, scholarship, and funding decisions are finally made.
