1 (b) Admissions or financial aid officers may not intentionally acquire this data by any alternative
2 means before admissions and financial aid, scholarship, and funding decisions are finally made.
3 (5)(4) There is established a private cause of action against any institution of higher education for a
4 violation of this section, directly or vicariously.
5 (6)(5) There is established a private cause of action against any officer, employee, or agent of an
6 institution of higher education for a violation of this section. However, if an officer, employee, or agent
7 performed an action in violation of subsection (2) or (4) at the direction of the institution or any other superior
8 officer, employee, or agent of the institution, the cause of action lies only against the institution or other superior
9 officer, employee, or agent of the institution.
10 (7)(6) In an action brought under this section against an institution of higher education by a
11 complaining applicant or student, the complaining applicant or student may recover:
12 (a) actual or compensatory damages sustained as a result of any violations of this section; and
13 (b) punitive damages against an institution if the complaining applicant or student demonstrates
14 that the institution of higher education discriminated against the complaining applicant or student intentionally or
15 with reckless indifference to the protected rights of the person.
16 (8)(7) In an action brought by a complaining applicant or student under this section, an institution of
17 higher education is strictly liable to the complaining applicant or student for $4,000 in statutory damages,
18 independent of any actual or compensatory damages sustained by the complaining applicant or student as a
19 result of the violation.
20 (a) In any action brought under this section, injunctive and declaratory relief is available to any
21 complaining applicant or student or to any organization suing on behalf of aggrieved applicants or students.
22 (b) In any action brought under this section, the state hereby waives sovereign immunity.
23 (9)(8) For the purposes of this section, "institution of higher education" means the Montana university
24 system, as defined in 20-25-201, and any eligible educational institution as defined in 20-26-1101.
25
26 NEW SECTION. Section 2. Codification instruction. [Section 1] is intended to be codified as a new
27 chapter in Title 20, and the provisions of Title 20 apply to [section 1].
